==English==
===Etymology===
Named after German [[mathematician]] [[w:Carl Gustav Jakob Jacobi|Carl Gustav Jakob Jacobi]].
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{numbertheory}} Mathematical function of two [[integer]]s, written <math>\left({a \over b}\right)</math>, based on whether ''a'' is a [[square]] [[modulo]] the [[prime factor]]s of ''b''.
